value.0:
Hello, <sir/madam>! Welcome to the Noway Inn! I'm Morgana. 

<StartAction>*offers a sweet smile*</Start>

Is there anything I can do for you?

And a pleasure to meet you, <FirstName>! We don't often get such polite  here. Tell me, is there anything I can do for you? 

<StartAction>*smiles again, more genuinely*</Start>

<StartAction>*smacks!*</Start> 

And here I thought you were different! Get out of here!

Mm, sorry , but William would have my head if I just left in the middle of the day. Maybe later, hm?

<StartAction>*gives a teasing smile, and a wink of her own*</Start>
I'll look forward to it. Enjoy your <quarterday> until then, <FirstName>.
Me? Well...um...I'm Morgana, like I said. I work here! It's not always such a nice place, truth be told. Lots of men grabbing at me all the time... But it pays well, and William's such a sweet man.
Oh, not at all! Some of them are even polite, and sweet, like you!
Oh, heavens no! He's too old for me, and not really my type. But he's good company, and I'd rather work for him than for even Lord Wiltun himself.
This is the Noway Inn, by William Bartleby. He's not always such a smart man, but he's kind, and wise, and by far the best person to work for in this town.
For you? I hope so. William will know for certain. If there's not, I'm sure we can find something for you.
You certainly can, <FirstName>! Whatever you like!
The Noway Inn is run by William Bartleby. That's him, over at the bar. He was almost stabbed once, a few years ago! Ever since then, he's worn that chain shirt.
I'm not sure, <sir/madam>. William would know, for certain, he runs this place.
Mr. Bartleby will be more than happy to get you whatever you need. I do hope you enjoy your time here!
A pleasure to meet you, Morgana. I'm <FirstName>.

<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start>You can meet me upstairs in ten minutes. 

<StartAction>*winks, and gives her rear a playful smack*</Start>
Ouch!
Alright... see you later!
I'm fine, thank you. But I'll be sure to come say goodbye before I leave.
I will!
I'd really like to know more about you, Morgana.
That's nice, Morgana. Enjoy your <quarterday>.
I should hope not everyone who comes in here acts like that!
Well, thank you, Morgana. You certainly deserve it.
Oh, are you and William...?
Alright, then. I'll keep that in mind.
Morgana, can you tell me a little about this place?
I'm glad you have a job here, then. Thank you, Morgana.
Are there any rooms available, Morgana?
I'll have a chat with him, then.
Can I get a drink, Morgana?
Ahh.. nice!
No, I'm fine, thank you.
Can you tell me a little about this place?
I see. Thank you.
Are there any rooms available?
Ah, I'll do just that, then.
Can I get a drink here?
Thank you. Pleasant <quarterday>.
